SIMPLE: inquire
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Inquire
<hw>In*quire"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Inquired</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Inquiring</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OE.
<ets>enqueren</ets>, <ets>inqueren</ets>, OF. <ets>enquerre</ets>, F.
<ets>enqu⟦eacute⟧rir</ets>, L. <ets>inquirere</ets>,
<ets>inquisitum</ets>; pref. <ets>in-</ets> in + <ets>quarere</ets> to
seek. See <er>Quest</er> a seeking, and cf. <er>Inquiry</er>.]</ety>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>enquire</asp>.]</altsp> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To
ask a question; to seek for truth or information by putting
queries.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>We will call the damsel, and <qex>inquire</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Gen.
xxiv. 57.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Then David <qex>inquired</qex> of the Lord yet again. And the Lord
answered him.</q> <rj><qau>1 Sam. xxiii. 4.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To seek to learn anything by recourse to the proper
means of knowledge; to make examination.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And <qex>inquire</qex>⟦br⟧
Gladly into the ways of God with man.</q>
<rj><qau>Miltom.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ This word is followed by <xex>of</xex> before the person
asked; as, to <xex>inquire</xex> of a neighbor. It is followed by
<xex>concerning</xex>, <xex>after</xex>, or <xex>about</xex>, before the
subject of inquiry; as, his friends <xex>inquired about or
concerning</xex> his welfare. ⟦ldquo⟧Thou dost not <xex>inquire</xex>
wisely <xex>concerning</xex> this.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Eccl. vii. 10.</au> It is
followed by <xex>into</xex> when search is made for particular knowledge
or information; as, to <xex>inquire into</xex> the cause of a sudden
death. It is followed by <xex>for</xex> or <xex>after</xex> when a place
or person is sought, or something is missing. ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Inquire</xex>
in the house of Judas <xex>for</xex> one called Saul of Tarsus.⟦rdquo⟧
<au>Acts ix. 11.</au></note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inquire</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Inquire
<hw>In*quire"</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To ask about; to
seek to know by asking; to make examination or inquiry
respecting.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Having thus at length <qex>inquired</qex> the truth concerning law
and dispense.</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And all obey and few <qex>inquire</qex> his will.</q>
<rj><qau>Byron.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To call or name.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- To ask; question. See
<er>Question</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inquirent</ent>⟦br⟧
